{"id":52,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":52,"title":"Chapter 48: Peace in America","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 48"],["h1","Peace in America"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p3"},"After Jesus returned to heaven, his disciples set up his Church throughout the land."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.1"},"4 Nephi 1:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p5"},"The people who repented of their sins were baptized and received the Holy Ghost."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.1"},"4 Nephi 1:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p7"},"Soon all the Nephites and Lamanites were converted. They did not argue and everyone was honest."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.2"},"4 Nephi 1:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p9"},"No one was rich or poor. The people shared everything, and they all had what they needed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.3"},"4 Nephi 1:3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p11"},"The disciples performed many miracles in the name of Jesus Christ. They healed the sick and brought the dead back to life."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.5"},"4 Nephi 1:5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p13"},"The people built new cities where others had been destroyed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.7"},"4 Nephi 1:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p15"},"They obeyed God’s commandments. They fasted and prayed and met together often to hear the word of God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.12"},"4 Nephi 1:12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p17"},"The people were happy."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.16"},"4 Nephi 1:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p19"},"There were no robbers, no liars, no murderers. The people were no longer divided into Nephites and Lamanites but were all one, the children of Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.16-17"},"4 Nephi 1:16–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p21"},"The Lord blessed the people in everything they did."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.18"},"4 Nephi 1:18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_052_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p23"},"They lived in peace for 200 years. The people became very rich."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-48-peace-in-america.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.22-23"},"4 Nephi 1:22–23"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
